  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "We should have two more `expectRevert` signatures:\r\n\r\n- `expectRevert(bytes4)` so you can do e.g. `expectRevert(Contract.CustomError.selector)`\r\n- `expectRevert(string)` so you can do e.g. `expectRevert(\"foo\")`\r\n\r\nCurrently you can achieve both of these but it requires casting and/or `abi.encodeWithSelector`",
